1.2  Electric Circuits and Current
 
Current is the time rate of flow of electric charge past a given point.

1.3 Systems of Units
1.4 Voltage
The voltage across an element is the work (energy) required to move a unit positive charge
from the - terminal to the + terminal.
The unit of voltage is the volt, V.
El voltaje es un concepto puntual.
1.5 Power and Energy
Power is the time rate of supplying or receiving power.
1. P = vi
Equivalentes:
De ley de Ohm:
V=ir
1. P=(ir)i=i^2r
De ley de Ohm:
i=v/r
1. P=v(v/r)=v^2/r
